fields.description:
Communication Type
The communication vehicle, e.g. email, phone call, or mailing

Channel Frequency
Use Channel Frequency to determine how frequently to connect with customers and prospects.
QUARTER, MONTH, and WEEK to determine frequency of communications.

Preference
Determines whether a customer or prospect has opted in or opted out of communications.
OPTIN or OPTOUT are valid codes

Preferred first name
Use this first name to address customer/prospect

First Name
A customer's given name–an informal name or nickname is commonly used

Phonetic First Name
First name transformed using the phonetic metaphone algorithm

Phonetic Last Name
Last name transformed using the phonetic metaphone algorithm

Nickname
Most common nickname for this given name–used for matching

Date of Birth
Optional–used both for segmentation and to send birthday cards and special offers

Value Status
Status of a customer based on lifetime purchases, flags VIP customers
